HEADWORD: Supercargo
<hw>Su`per*car"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Super-</ets> + <ets>cargo</ets>: cf. Sp.
<ets>sobrecargo.</ets> Cf. <er>Surcharge</er>.]</ety> <def>An officer or
person in a merchant ship, whose duty is to manage the sales, and
superintend the commercial concerns, of the voyage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

